Philippine Stock Movers: Cebu Air, Security Bank, Vista Land

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-25T04:28:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/philippine-stock-movers-cebu-air-security-bank-vista-land.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.3 percent to
4,331.37, the highest level since Nov. 5. The measure is 1.5
percent away from its 4,397.30 record close on Nov. 4.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  , the nationâ€™s biggest budget
carrier, decreased 1.9 percent to 78.40 pesos, ending a two-day,
4 percent rally after the Philippine Stock Exchange said 398.6
million shares of the company previously under lock-up will be
eligible for trading starting April 27.  Security Bank Corp. (SECB)   advanced 5 percent to 95.50
pesos, the highest close since Nov. 23. The lender will replace
 China Banking Corp. (CHIB)  in the benchmark Philippine Stock Exchange
Index starting on May 9, the bourse said in a statement posted
on its website on April 20.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)  , a builder of homes,
climbed 2 percent to 3.13 pesos, the highest level since Jan. 7.
The company said its low-cost housing unit plans to sell 12
billion pesos ($278 million) of projects this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
